Disk Usage and System Monitoring refers to the set of tools and practices used to observe the resource consumption and operational health of a Linux system.

df (disk free) - report the amount of the disk space used and available on mounted filesystem.It's used for checking overall partition capacity
du (disk usage) - This command estimates the file space usage of a specific directory or file.it's used for locating where space is being consumed within a partition.
free - it display the total amount of the free and used physical and swap memory in the system ,along with the buffers and caches by the kernel.
uptime - it shows the overall operational status of the system
    The current time
    The time the system has been running since the last reboot (uptime).
    The average system load over the last 1, 5, and 15 minutes (a measure of how many processes are waiting for CPU time).

